<div class="comments-body">
<p>lol, rack is "better" for crisp flavour. Granted if you prefer the greasy mush, then fry it in a pan.</p>

<p>It can take twice as long to cook it on a rack, and you don't need to preheat. As with most meats, such as steak, or pork roast, when it's cooked in an oven the meat becomes more flavourful, and has that "fall off the bone quality". Bacon is no exception, though its texture will be different than that of a pork roast, but i gurantee you that cooking it properly on a rack is better for texture, and flavour than frying, regardless if it's being fried in an oven or in a pan.</p>
<span class="comments-post">Posted by: Delusional at January 20, 2011 09:37 AM</span>
